    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-06T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="660"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d660">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811B.01/496: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-06T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 6, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2383. Your 3207, November 2, 2 p.m. The Department wishes you without delay to
                    approach the Spanish Government for certain concessions, either in a personal
                    conversation with Count Jordana or, <pb facs="0744" n="732" xml:id="pg_732"/> if
                    you deem it preferable, in a conversation your Counselor may have with an
                    appropriate high official of the Spanish Government. Among the particular
                    concessions desired at this time are those set forth in the immediately
                    following telegram no. 2384.<note n="5" xml:id="d660fn5">November 6, 6 p.m.,
                            <ref target="#pg_648">p. 648</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
